Police are searching for the suspects involved in the murder of Polokwane Ocean Basket franchise owner, Lizette Deacon and her mother. Police spokesperson Motlafela Mojapelo reported on the incident. Courtesy of #DStv403 LIMPOPO - Police continue to investigate what appears to be a twin murder in Polokwane in Limpopo where the bodies of Lizette Deacon and her mother Hettie were found. Deacon was the owner of both Ocean Basket franchises in Polokwane. Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said when police arrived at the initial crime scene they discovered blood traces and stains. READ: Specialised police unit re-established "We immediately launched a search operation for both the victims and the suspects and ultimately, last night, the victims were found along the R37 road. They were stuffed in the boot of the car and they were both tied up." No arrests have been made at this point and police are searching for the suspects. The motive for the killings remains unknown but police say they are not ruling out robbery as a motive. Grace Harding, the CEO of the Ocean Basket Group, comments on the double murder of Lizette Deacon and her mother, Hettie. Courtesy of #DStv403 Grace Harding, the CEO of the Ocean Basket Group, attended a gathering at the Mall of the North. Residents came together to demonstrate against crime in the area. "Our focus now is on supporting the staff," Harding said. " These two women were more than just franchise owners or managers, they were mothers and daughters to all the staff -- the 70 people who they provided jobs for."